                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#16v" facs="017">Fol. 16v</locus><desc>Crude drawing of the head of a woman</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#56r" facs="056">Fol. 56r</locus><desc>Saint <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName>, the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#56v" facs="057">Fol. 56v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>: Saint George spearing a <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/></desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#ms_i1">Fols. ms_i1, </locus>
                    <locus target="#1r #5r #8v #14r #16r #23v #26r #27r #30v #33r #35r #36v #39r" facs="001 005 009 014 016 024 026 027 031 033 035 037 039">1r, 5r, 8v, 14r, 16r, 23v, 26r, 27r, 30v, 33r, 35r, 36v, 39r</locus>
                    <desc>The Homilies: Ḫǝdar, Taḫśaś, Ṭǝrr, Yäkkatit, Mäggabit, Miyazya, Gǝnbot, Säne, Ḥamle, Näḥase, Mäskäräm, Ṭǝqǝmt, Ḫǝdar (for a second time)</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#ms_i1">Fols. ms_i1, </locus>
                    <locus target="#44v 45v 47v 48v 49v 50v 51r 51v 53v 55r" facs="045 046 048 049 050 051 052 054 055">44v,, ,, ,, ,, , </locus>
                    <desc>The Miracles: Ḫǝdar (There is none assigned for the month of Ḫǝdar; apparently the homiliy repeated above was intended to serve as a miracle), Taḫśaś, Ṭǝrr, Yäkkatit, Mäggabit, Miyazya, Gǝnbot, Säne, Ḥamle, Näḥase, Mäskäräm, Ṭǝqǝmt</desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#Inside cover" facs="001">Fols. Inside, </locus>
                    <desc>
                    There is a mirror niche carved into the inside front cover
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#33r #5r #23v #35r #1r" facs="033 005 024 035 001">Fols. 33r, 5r, 23v, 35r, 1r</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Copied for <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ ሚካኤል</foreign>, Walda Mika’el (33r). Later owners: <foreign xml:lang="gez">አመተ ሥላሴ</foreign>, Amata Selassie (prayer, 5r); <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሠርፀ ተንሣኤ</foreign>, Sarsa Tensae (23v and 35r); and Capt. W. W. Edwards, Transport Train 18th Gurkas(?) Light Cavalry (1r)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    This entry employs some information from Macomber, William F. “Catalogue of oriental manuscripts in the library of Seabury-Western Theological Seminary, Evanston, Illinois.” Le Muséon 92 (1979) 369–386
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment. Simple wooden boards, with the front board broken and stitched together.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
